#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:5
msgid "C setjmp-longjmp Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:7
msgid ""
"setjmp-longjmp support is enabled by default in Emscripten. This is "
"controlled by the ``SUPPORT_LONGJMP`` setting, which can take these values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:10
msgid "``emscripten``: JavaScript-based support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:11
msgid "``wasm``: WebAssembly exception handling-based support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:12
msgid "0: No support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:13
msgid ""
"1: Default support, depending on the exception mode. ``wasm`` if ``-fwasm-"
"exceptions`` is used, ``emscripten`` otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:15
msgid ""
"If :ref:`native Wasm exceptions <webassembly-exception-handling-based-"
"support>` are used, ``SUPPORT_LONGJMP`` defaults to ``wasm``, and if :ref:"
"`JavaScript-based exceptions <javascript-based-exception-support>` are used "
"or no exception support is used, it defaults to ``emscripten``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:20
msgid ""
"``setjmp`` saves information about the calling environment into a buffer, "
"and ``longjmp`` transfers the control back to the point where ``setjmp`` was "
"called by using the buffer. ``longjmp``'s call stack should contain the "
"function from which ``setjmp`` was called."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:25
msgid ""
"Emscripten's support has a restriction that indirect calls to ``setjmp`` are "
"not supported. For example, the below does not work:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:36
msgid "JavaScript-based setjmp-longjmp Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:38
msgid ""
"In this mode, Emscripten emulates setjmp-longjmp using JavaScript. This "
"option is set by adding ``-sSUPPORT_LONGJMP=emscripten`` to the command "
"line, but this is currently enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:42
msgid ""
"Note that this option can have relatively high overhead in terms of code "
"size, but it will work on all JavaScript engines with WebAssembly support, "
"even if they do not yet support the `new WebAssembly exception handling "
"proposal <https://github.com/WebAssembly/exception-handling/blob/master/"
"proposals/exception-handling/Exceptions.md>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:49
msgid "WebAssembly Exception Handling-based setjmp-longjmp Support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:51
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can opt-in to the new support using the `WebAssembly "
"exception handling <https://github.com/WebAssembly/exception-handling/blob/"
"master/proposals/exception-handling/Exceptions.md>`_ proposal. To enable it, "
"pass ``-sSUPPORT_LONGJMP=wasm`` at both compile time and link time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:57
msgid ""
"This option leverages a new feature that brings built-in instructions for "
"throwing and catching exceptions to WebAssembly. As a result, it can reduce "
"code size and performance overhead compared to the JavaScript-based "
"implementation. This option is currently supported in several major web "
"browsers, but `may not be supported in all WebAssembly engines yet <https://"
"webassembly.org/roadmap/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:68
msgid "Using Exceptions and setjmp-longjmp Together"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:70
msgid ""
"We also have two kinds of :ref:`exception handling support <exceptions>`: "
"JavaScript-based support and the new WebAssembly EH-based support. Our "
"setjmp-longjmp support use the same mechanisms. Because of that, when they "
"are used together, the kind of setjmp-longjmp support will be determined by "
"the EH support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:76
msgid ""
"For example, to use the JavaScript-based EH and setjmp-longjmp support "
"together:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:82
msgid "To use the WebAssembly EH and setjmp-longjmp support together:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:88
msgid ""
"``-sSUPPORT_LONGJMP``, which defaults to ``emscripten`` or ``wasm`` "
"depending on the exception mode, is enabled by default, so you don't need to "
"pass it explicitly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:92
msgid ""
"But you need to pass ``-sSUPPORT_LONGJMP=wasm`` at compile time explicitly "
"before you link C and C++ code together, because you don't use exception "
"flags at C compile time, but it needs to match the setjmp-longjmp handling "
"model of the C++ code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:103
msgid ""
"There is one specific restriction for using WebAssembly EH-based support for "
"exceptions and setjmp-longjmp at the same time. You cannot call ``setjmp`` "
"within a C++ ``catch`` clause. For example, the following will error out "
"during compile time:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/setjmp-longjmp.rst:116
msgid ""
"Calling ``setjmp`` within a ``try`` clause is fine. Calling another user "
"function that calls ``setjmp`` within a ``catch`` clause is also fine."
msgstr ""
